<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1441,195,1563]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,351,1475,1499]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Remark</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Perez-Gelabert" authorityYear="2008" box="[366,584,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Efferia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vinalensis">
<emphasis box="[366,584,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Efferia vinalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to the couplet containing 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hine)" baseAuthorityName="Hine" box="[968,1227,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Erax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[968,1142,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Ef. nigritarsis</emphasis>
(Hine)
</taxonomicName>
in Bromley’s key (1929) but is distinguished from that species by the yellow vestiture of the face, the 2-3 yellow lateral bristles on the scutum, and the combined characters of the terminalia (Fig. 46-48).
</paragraph>
